# Code of Conduct

## Our commitment

This repository is maintained as a respectful, harassment-free collaboration space.
All contributors are expected to communicate constructively and act professionally.

## Expected behavior

- Be respectful, specific, and outcome-focused.
- Assume good intent and ask clarifying questions.
- Accept feedback and resolve disagreements without personal attacks.
- Keep discussions aligned to repository goals.

## Unacceptable behavior

- Harassment, hate speech, threats, or intimidation.
- Repeated hostile behavior or trolling.
- Sharing private information without consent.
- Sexualized language or unwanted attention.

## Reporting

If you experience or witness unacceptable behavior:

1. Contact maintainers privately using channels listed in [SUPPORT.md](SUPPORT.md).
2. Include links, timestamps, and relevant context.
3. Avoid posting sensitive personal information publicly.

Primary maintainer contact: `{{ maintainer_handle }}`.

## Enforcement

Maintainers may remove comments, lock threads, or block accounts for policy violations.
Consequences may range from warning to permanent ban based on severity and repetition.

